2.1 Confidentiality Obligations. The Recipient shall maintain the confidentiality of the Confidential Information and shall take all reasonable and appropriate security precautions to preserve such confidentiality, which shall include employing a degree of care and security measures at least as protective as those the Recipient applies to its own confidential information of a similar nature.

2.2 Use of Confidential Information. The Recipient may utilize the Confidential Information solely to fulfill its obligations under this Agreement and for no other purpose unless expressly authorized in writing by the Discloser. The Recipient shall only disclose the Confidential Information to its personnel who require access for the performance of their duties in relation to the purposes permitted herein and shall ensure that such personnel are bound by written confidentiality undertakings no less stringent than those contained in this Agreement.

2.3 Prohibited Actions. The Recipient shall not:
(a) reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble any software or other technological material that constitutes part of the Confidential Information;
(b) use the Confidential Information in any manner that could cause harm or loss to the Discloser.

2.4 Notification of Unauthorized Actions. The Recipient shall promptly inform the Discloser upon becoming aware of any unauthorized:
(a) loss;
(b) disclosure;
(c) breach of confidentiality; or
(d) use or misappropriation of the Confidential Information, in accordance with applicable laws.

2.5 Exclusions from Confidentiality. The obligations of confidentiality set forth herein shall not apply to information that:
(a) was already known to the Recipient prior to its disclosure by the Discloser without an obligation of confidentiality;
(b) is or becomes publicly available through no fault of the Recipient;
(c) is independently developed by the Recipient without reference to the Confidential Information provided by the Discloser;
(d) is received from a third party not under an obligation of confidentiality; or
(e) is disclosed with the prior written consent of the Discloser's authorized representative.

2.6 Handling of Personal Information. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, the Discloser shall not provide any personal information to the Recipient unless specifically requested by the Recipient. The Discloser shall comply with all applicable laws regarding any personal information provided to the Recipient under this Agreement.
